<dl id="n29220e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n29" href="#n29220e">N29 (VI.B.21)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n29all.htm#n29220e"> 220(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> See him in a / proper light</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">&lsquo; &hellip; I told him in very bad Russian that I had offered thirty once, but wouldn&apos;t again; but this, oddly enough, did not pacify him &hellip; finally Mr. Muir himself came out and gave him the substance of it sharply and shortly&mdash;but he failed to <mark>see it in a proper light</mark>. Some people are very hard to please.&rsquo; <small> Stuart Dodgson Collingwood, <a name="SDCL" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#SDCL"><cite title="source">The Life and Letters of Lewis Carroll</cite></a> ([1912]) 106-107</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
